activity.value: Octopus Investments is a diversified investment firm specializing in alternative asset classes, catering to both retail and institutional clients.  They focus on impact investing, aligning their investments with three core themes: empowering people, revitalizing healthcare, and building a sustainable planet. For retail investors, they offer a range of products including Venture Capital Trusts (VCTs), Enterprise Investment Schemes (EISs), Business Relief-qualifying investments, and listed UK small and medium-sized company funds.  These products cater to diverse investment goals, from wealth preservation and succession planning to supporting social impact initiatives.  On the institutional side, Octopus Investments offers specialized asset management services across five key areas: renewable energy, sustainable infrastructure, real estate, healthcare, and venture capital. This approach allows them to meet the specific mandates of institutional investors, often focused on ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) factors.

activity.value: Aayan Medical Imaging Ltd. operates within the medical technology and equipment distribution sector, specializing in the global supply of innovative diagnostic equipment. The company focuses on providing a comprehensive solution for healthcare providers, encompassing the sale, installation, and maintenance of advanced imaging technologies, including Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI), Computed Tomography (CT), Positron Emission Tomography (PET) scanners, Cardiac Catheterization Labs, Ultrasound, Digital Mammography, X-Ray, and Dual-energy X-ray Absorptiometry (DXA) scanning. Aayan Medical Imaging Ltd. leverages its extensive network within European national health industries to offer cutting-edge medical technology, ensuring the delivery of high-quality equipment and services to support both healthcare providers and their patients. The company's mobile site solutions enable the deployment of these advanced scanners in various locations, expanding access to diagnostic services and enhancing patient care.
